    "At the end of the retraction phase, E k reaches a second local minimum, after which the droplet enters a second spreading phase in which E k rises again to reach a third local maximum (6).",
    "Simultaneously, E g decreases further and reaches a local minimum corresponding to the oscillation minimum (7).",
    "This energy exchange continues throughout the damped oscillations of the droplet and is in good qualitative agreement with the simulation.",
    "Overall, VcPINNs capture the droplet dynamics in a physically consistent manner, further indicated by the long-term subsiding of E k and growth of E d. As a cumulative quantity, E d should ideally increase monotonically and thus serves as an indicator for energy conservation of the predictions.",
